	<pb facs="liv_002484_0001" n="0001"/><!-- Change both @facs and @n -->
	<!-- Start each page with a <pb> formatted as above -->
<!-- If this is a letter or similar with an opener (with content such as dateline and/or salute) add it. For example: -->
<opener>
<lb/><add place="inspace" rend="left gray small" hand="#U1">5-6-9</add><!-- diagonal --> <dateline rend="right"><placeName><geogName type="island">Zanzibar</geogName></placeName> <date when="1866-03-14">14 March <add place="above" rend="right gray small" hand="#U1">MS 8/14</add>
<lb rend="right"/>1866</date></dateline>
<lb/><salute>My Dear <persName>Sunley</persName></salute><!-- Change line info as appropriate -->
</opener>
<lb/><p><space extent="7" unit="chars"/>Having <choice><sic>recieved</sic><corr>received</corr></choice> no
<lb/>letter from you till I was
<lb/>on the point of leaving
<lb/><placeName><settlement type="city">Bombay</settlement></placeName> I took some
<lb/><orgName>sepoys</orgName> &amp; <term type="people">Africans</term>,
<lb/>but I would have <w>pre-
<lb break="no"/>ferred</w> the whole to have
<lb/>been <orgName><placeName><geogName type="island">Johanna</geogName></placeName> men</orgName> 
<lb/>I took your silence as
<lb/>evidence that you could
<lb/>not get what I wanted    
                
    <pb facs="liv_002484_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>I am glad to <choice><sic>recieve</sic><corr>receive</corr></choice> the
<lb/>men you sent and though
<lb/>the pay is higher than I
<lb/>intended it is all right.
<lb/>It only makes it a little
<lb/><choice><sic>ackward</sic><corr cert="high">awkward</corr></choice> for me with
<lb/>the others because the 
<lb/>others are at 5 &amp; your
<lb/>friends will tell that
<lb/>they get 7 However I
<lb/>shall make the best of it
<lb/>and I thank you for
<lb/>the trouble you took in
<lb/>the matter. This <persName>Musa</persName> 
<lb/>was not a bad one &amp;
<lb/>I was glad to see him again

    <pb facs="liv_002484_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/>I was glad to see old <persName><unclear cert="medium">Seedy</unclear></persName>
<lb/>again. I hope you will
<lb/>soon make a lot of money
<lb/>and set yourself free to
<lb/>follow your own bent.
<lb/>One cannot always do the
<lb/>good he would. We are
<lb/>led very often &amp; have to
<lb/>confess that there is a
<lb/>Divinity that shapes our
<lb/>ends, rough hew them
<lb/>how we will <!--What is this punctuation? -AA --><!-- I think it's an equal sign, one of DL's usual methods --><unclear cert="medium">=</unclear> I can
<lb/>sympathize sincerely
<lb/>with all earnest <unclear cert="medium">workers</unclear>
<lb/>whether successful ones
<lb/>or not -</p>
    
    <pb facs="liv_002484_0004" n="0004"/>
<lb/><p>I shall attend to the Â£29-2-11 <add place="below inspace" hand="#U2"><date when="1844-03-14">March 14 1866</date></add>
<lb/>which was advanced for <add place="below inspace" hand="#U2"><persName>Livingstone</persName></add> <!-- There appears to be some text between these two lines. I cannot make it out. The name "Livingstone" appears to be written between the next two lines. I am not sure how to encode this. JM --><!-- Done. AW -->
<lb/>me. The journal was
<lb/>what I wanted. It will <add place="below inspace" hand="#U2"><choice><abbr>Rec<hi rend="sup">d</hi></abbr><expan>Received</expan></choice> <date when="1844-03-31">31 March</date></add> <!-- "Received" together with the date 31 March is written between the next two lines. Please advise on how to encode this. JM --><!-- Done. AW -->
<lb/>do for reference &amp;	<add place="below inspace" hand="#U2"><gap extent="1" unit="words" agent="illegible"/></add>
<lb/>waste paper &amp; that was
<lb/>all I wanted.</p>
<lb/><p><persName>Dr. Kirk</persName> comes out here
<lb/>soon as successor to <persName>Dr.
<lb/>Seward</persName>. My brother is
<lb/>at <placeName><unclear cert="medium">Fernando</unclear></placeName> <unclear>&amp;</unclear> <persName>Meller</persName>
<lb/>you know is at <placeName><geogName type="island"><w>Mada<supplied>-</supplied>
<lb break="no"/>-gascar</w></geogName></placeName>. My son perished
<lb/>at <placeName><settlement type="town">Richmond</settlement></placeName>. <unclear><subst><del><gap extent="1" unit="words"/></del><add place="over-text">We</add></subst></unclear> only know
<lb/>that he was captured by the
<lb/>confederates.</p> <closer><salute>Very sincerely your</salute>
<lb/><space extent="6" unit="chars"/><signed><persName>David Livingstone</persName></signed></closer>
    
